  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">START FUND - Emergency Flood Response Lower Shabelle, Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This response seeks to provide Unconditional Multipurpose Cash Transfers to 1,000 of the most vulnerable households that are severely affected by the flood in Afgoye District. The transfer will be made via mobile money transfer, which ensures efficiency and transparency, is cost-effective and enables mitigation of protection risks. UCTs will improve beneficiaries&apos; access to food and other basic needs including safe water, medicine/healthcare, and shelter, while also preventing HHs from resorting to negative coping mechanisms, which erode resilience in the longer term. The proposed rate of $60 per HH is in line with the minimum expenditure basket for Lower Shabelle, aligned with the value endorsed by the Somalia Cash Working Group that Concern is leading. The flood mitigation/protection work will strengthen the river bank that will further reduce the flood risks in the communities safeguarding large communities on the risk areas. The sand bags will placed at three river breakage points by the community volunteers, In response to the current COVID-19 situation, the action will implement hygiene messaging through risk communication by the trained Community Hygiene Promoters. During the sand bags laying handwashing stations will be installed in the sites so that volunteers will have access to water and soap. Similarly, the implementation approach will be aligned with the COVID-19 adaptation plan such as avoid large gatherings, social distancing, household verification and registration including post distribution monitoring through telephone.</narrative>
  </description>
